# ESLint Configuration Rules

## Core Principles
- **Strict Mode**: Enforce code quality and consistency
- **React/TypeScript Focus**: Configure for React 18 + TypeScript
- **Auto-Fix**: Enable fixable rules for better DX

## Key Rules
- **react-refresh/only-export-components**: Warn (enable Fast Refresh)
- **@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars**: Error with args exception
- **react-hooks/exhaustive-deps**: Warn (enforce dependency arrays)

## Best Practices
- Use `warn` for style issues, `error` for bugs
- Override base rules only when necessary
- Document non-obvious rule configurations
- Keep rules consistent with Prettier

## Anti-Patterns
- Don't disable TypeScript strict checks globally
- Avoid too many rule overrides (signals architectural issues)
- Don't use `eslint-disable` comments excessively
